import org.apache.spark.mllib.clustering.{KMeans, KMeansModel}
import org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.Vectors
import org.apache.spark.mllib.random.RandomRDDs._
parsedData: org.apache.spark.rdd.RDD[org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.Vector] = MapPartitionsRDD[1] at map at <console>:37
numClusters: Int = 4
numIterations: Int = 20
clusters: org.apache.spark.mllib.clustering.KMeansModel = org.apache.spark.mllib.clustering.KMeansModel@31c29888

paragraphs.text:
val evalData = parsedData.collect.map(d=>(d, clusters.predict(d)))
println("%table x\ty\tcluster")
evalData.foreach(r=>
    println(Seq(r._1(0), r._1(1), r._2).mkString("\t"))
)

// put data into shared resource pool to send it python side
z.put("kmeansData", evalData.map(r=>Seq(r._1(0), r._1(1), r._2).toArray))

%pyspark
# get data from shared resource pool
data = z["kmeansData"]

%pyspark import matplotlib.pyplot as plt # helper function to display in Zeppelin import StringIO def show(p): img = StringIO.StringIO() p.savefig(img, format='svg') img.seek(0) print "%html
" + img.buf + "
"

%pyspark

plt.clf()
data = z.get("kmeansData")
x = []
y = []
k = []

for i in range(0, len(data)):
    x.append(data[i][0])
    y.append(data[i][1])
    k.append(data[i][2])

plt.scatter(x,y, c=k, alpha=0.5)
show(plt)
